Two consignments with 270 lobster were seized at the Cape Town International Airport this week. CAPE TOWN - Western Cape police are investigating a case of possible illegal export of live lobster worth R250,000. Two consignments with 270 lobster were seized at the Cape Town International Airport this week by Fisheries Department officials as well as border police.It s suspected the cargo, headed to Hong Kong via Johannesburg, is in violation of the Living Marine Resources Act as there was no permit for the export.The police s Frederick van Wyk says fisheries officials confiscated the lobster. The lobsters are being kept at the SAA crew rooms because they are live. The permit holder was notified of the seizure of the product and we ve opened an inquiry for further investigation. 